From 9b8596f5303746eb54e12280e4d2020dce999447 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 21:59:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Redesign UI: rotary knobs, lever switches, wide compact
 layout
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Full mechanical-device makeover replacing the tall slider stack:
- Custom rotary knob widget (vertical drag = value, Shift = fine, double-click
  resets) with a rim value-arc and pointer. Every FloatParam is now a knob.
- Compact vertical 3-position lever switch (up/middle/down) with per-position
  labels and a caption — used for SOFT/HARD/FOLD and OFF/2x/4x oversampling.
- Framed module panels (PITCH, AMP, SHAPE, EQ, TRANSIENT, OUTPUT, SEQ) arranged
  in two horizontal rows instead of a single tall column.
- Transport + WAV export moved into the title bar.
- Window changed from 340x1050 (way too tall) to 720x430 (wide and short).

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
